      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(config): add XDG and GOG path overrides",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR implements the #621/#622 path model as one change:\n\n- Add kind-aware config/data/state/cache path resolution with `GOG_HOME`, per-kind `GOG_CONFIG_DIR`, `GOG_DATA_DIR`, `GOG_STATE_DIR`, `GOG_CACHE_DIR`, and global `--home`.\n- Move new auth metadata, file-keyring data, service-account keys, tracking state, Gmail watch state, and backup/cache state to the correct kind-specific roots.\n- Preserve legacy reads for normal migration, but keep explicit `GOG_HOME`/per-kind overrides isolated so CI, containers, and agents do not silently import host secrets/state.\n- Keep Drive/Gmail download defaults unchanged unless the command already has its own output flag.\n- Document path precedence, XDG behavior, compatibility rules, and container/systemd usage.\n\n## Compatibility notes\n\n- Relative `GOG_*_DIR` and `--home` values are rejected; relative XDG values are ignored per XDG expectations.\n- Legacy OAuth credentials, service-account keys, file-keyring directories, tracking config, backup config, and Gmail watch files remain readable when no explicit gog-specific override is active.\n- Explicit gog-specific roots intentionally skip legacy secret/state fallback to preserve sandbox isolation.\n- `--home` also affects root help path output, not only command execution.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `make ci`\n- Focused regression tests across `internal/config`, `internal/cmd`, `internal/googleapi`, `internal/backup`, and `internal/tracking`\n- Live smoke: isolated `GOG_HOME` writes credentials metadata to `GOG_HOME/data`, config path to `GOG_HOME/config`, keeps `client_secret` out of metadata, and lists the keyring-backed client\n- Live smoke: legacy credentials in the old config dir still list and remove when no explicit data override is set\n- Autoreview: `/Users/steipete/Projects/agent-scripts/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\nCloses #621.\nCloses #622.\n\nThanks @alexminza for the original proposal and direction.\n",
        "branch": "feat/xdg-gog-home-paths",
